<br>
They changed his pathing.  Used to wander around the upper rooms, now he warps into the middle pillar.<br>
<br>
Use a monk to hold him (and usually die in under 2 seconds), then ranger moves him to a corner where you do a max range beat down.<br>
<br>
Just a question of DPS and healing at that point.<br>
<br>
Ironfang <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2F2F4F><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/bthesteelwarrior.showUserPublicProfile?gid=thehawnz>the hawnz</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>is a Formidable Opponent</span><br>  Posts: 197<br> <font color=#FF0000>(3/26/03 11:36 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.steelwarrior.org/forum/p_die.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re: ...</span><hr size=1> <!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>but once the ranger dies how do you keep the #1 rampage from being the MT?<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
